Translate books using artificial intelligence and Google

such as the book ↓
This book was for teaching English and was of poor quality. 20 It is en and not
Arabic. What was required was its Arabic translation, but it is an English educational
book. The original pages are important. The user of the book must know what is on
the main page and its meaning in the original pages in English. I corrected the book
again so that there is a page on the right in English that corresponds to it on the
same page, translated and separate from it. That is, the pages are not combined.
That is, the traditional methods were not used in order to be able to print correctly
with the correct numbering.
I translated this book manually because Google Translate was translating the codes
and changing their colors, which is not required, so I decomposed the file and
translated it manually using the AI ​​tool built into one of the translation programs.
Now the translation problem has been solved. The rest of the problem of the large
number of pages, I used programming scripts from one of the programs and some
other tools such as Adobe Acrobat, PDF X, 7 PDF and others, even to print a very
small booklet of 8 pages per page on both sides, as the book was printed on 25
sheets printed in duplex (on both sides). It was cut, assembled and given to the
printer. It was skinned and became a very small book, but also professional. This
was also useful in public transportation for reading and easy to carry as well. It is a
good way to learn and get away from distractions. There are many of these
examples of printing skills.
